on wednesday breeden said safety mechanisms called 
circuitbreakers automatic temporary trading halts in times of 
market volatility have eliminated much of the need for officials 
to halt trading 
breeden told the telecommunications and finance subcommittee of 
the house energy and commerce committee that he believed the 
possibility of arbitrary halts could cause uncertainty and 
volatility in the markets the power to make such a decision should 
remain where it is now with the president he contended 
brady in a letter accompanying his testimony said however 
that he believed the change is needed 
the initial governmental response to market emergencies should 
