the figures show a sharp drop in the last two years in the 
number of federal indictments for violations of federal obscenity 
laws while childpornography charges soared during the same time 
period 
indictments for federal obscenity violations dropped from 66 in 
1987 to 37 last year according to figures compiled by the 
departments national obscenity enforcement unit 
the figures may not be complete because us attorneys are not 
required to report obscenity prosecutions said spokesman joseph 
krovisky 
but fbi figures reflect a similar trend 
the number of obscenity cases pending at the bureau dropped from 
355 in 1987 to 302 in 1988 and to 194 in the first nine months of 
the 1989 fiscal year which ended sept 30 
