<TEXT>
head injuries caused 2 percent of all deaths in 
the united states in a recent sevenyear period and the most 
common causes were auto crashes guns and falls according to 
doctors who studied such deaths 
the death rate for americans with head injuries was 169 per 
100000 people from 1979 through 1986 said dr daniel m sosin and 
his colleagues at the division of injury epidemiology and control 
of the centers for disease control in atlanta 
they reported in todays edition of the journal of the american 
medical association that they identified 315328 deaths associated 
with head injuries 
of those injuries 57 percent were suffered in motor vehicle 
accidents most commonly among people younger than 35 the 
physicians said 
whites ages 15 to 24 had a death rate of 227 per 100000 from 
head injuries suffered in motor vehicle accidents the researchers 
said blacks of the same age group had a death rate of 92 per 
100000 from vehicle accidents 
another 14 percent of the fatal head injuries were caused by 
guns 
among blacks ages 25 to 34 homicides by firearm caused 42 
deaths per 100000 more than five times the rate for whites in 
the same age group 
the death rate for head injuries from suicidal gunshot wounds 
however was much higher for whites of all ages 164 per 100000 
than it was for blacks with a rate of 065 per 100000 
falls were the third most common cause of fatal head injuries 
accounting for 12 percent of the total the physicians found they 
also found that the death rate for falls rose with the age of the 
populace 
the sharpest rise came after age 75 sosin said with 206 
deaths per 100000 for males in the oldest age group and 113 per 
100000 for women 
