serious condition in intensive care at community general 
osteopathic hospital in harrisburg with multiple fractures the 
condition of the others ranged from fair to good hospital 
officials said 
freeman said six of the 10 cellblocks were damaged extensively 
and the commissary was destroyed in wednesdays riot 
this weeks uprisings were the latest in a series of problems 
within pennsylvanias prison system a federal judge in august 
ordered the state to close part of the western penitentiary in 
pittsburgh because of unsafe and unconstitutional conditions 
the state is challenging that ruling and the prison remains open 
