police stormed an overcrowded state prison 
this morning to regain control from inmates who seized hostages and 
set fires in a twonight riot that left more than 100 people 
injured authorities said 
officers fired shots and tear gas in a kitchen building 
wounding one inmate in the assault that led to retaking of control 
less than two hours later at 935 am said ken robinson state 
corrections department spokesman 
hospital officials said that at some point a guard and two 
prisoners were critically injured 
police in riot gear and wielding shotguns pushed surrendering or 
captured prisoners to the ground holding them facedown in the 
grass 
rioters among about 1900 inmates who remained loose in their 
cellblocks this morning were taken to a holding area at the rear of 
the prison grounds robinson said 
there was continuing confusion about the numbers of rioters 
injuries and hostages in the rampages that started wednesday night 
officials initially said there were eight hostages later it was 
reported there were four and that all were released safely 
throughout the night and this morning but a fifth hostage was 
found after order was restored officials said 
more than 100 people were injured including 60 thursday night 
and this morning robinson said he said there were no deaths and 
all employees are accounted for 
