have been caused by overcrowding and inmates resentment over 
policy changes 
inmates were upset by a decision not to allow families to bring 
in food during extended familyday visits officials said the food 
could be used to conceal drugs cash and other contraband 
a new medical policy that prisoners objected to actually 
improves access to care but inmates viewed the change as an 
attempt to restrict health care freeman said adding that the 
staff could have done a better job explaining the changes the 
change involved assigning routine examinations to certain days 
camp hill is about 45 percent over capacity and the entire state 
prison system is about 48 percent over capacity 
attorney general ernie preate jr said the disturbance at camp 
hill 4 miles west of harrisburg and a smaller uprising at 
huntingdon state prison on monday were the predictable result of 
a prison crowding crisis that has been allowed to fester for too 
long 
