guerrillas who are fighting to establish an islamic republic in 
afghanistan 
the soviets have withdrawn from afghanistan said the 
chinese official that was our main goal we see no need to 
continue our support of the guerrillas 
diplomats said they were not sure how the end of chinas support 
would affect the guerrillas ability to fight 
china began supplying the rebel forces soon after the soviet 
union intervened in afghanistan a decade ago chinesemade ak47 
automatic weapons along with chinese mortars small rockets 
grenades and other light arms were the weapons of choice for many 
of the rebel bands diplomats said 
chinese support never reached the level of american assistance 
which hovers at an estimated 600 million a year asian diplomats 
predicted that rebel forces would continue to be supplied with 
chinese arms but that they would be purchased on the international 
arms market 
one highranking asian diplomat whose country has good 
relations with afghanistan said his embassy believed chinese arms 
supplies stopped sometime this summer 
everything in the pipeline was delivered he said but 
they made no new commitments 
he said the policy shift was in line with recent changes in 
chinas foreign policy 
now that china and the soviet union are normalizing relations 
and chinas ties are also improving with india beijing does not 
see the need to encourage a civil war in afghanistan he said 
in addition he said since the crackdown on the prodemocracy 
movement in beijing chinese foreign policy has taken on a more 
cautious air 
they are very concerned again with their relations with other 
socialist countries he said we perceive this as part of the 
chinese leaderships renewed emphasis on politics 
the chinese diplomat said trade relations have begun with 
afghanistan china is selling canned goods and some light 
industrial products he also noted the afghan government has 
stopped criticizing chinas policy toward the war 
indeed the foreign ministry no longer mentions china when it 
discusses the supporters of the guerrillas 
