mosquitoes are the latest scourge to 
follow in the wake of hurricane hugo but the air force reserve is 
coming to the rescue with an aerial bombardment on the pests this 
weekend 
the air force will use c130 airplanes to swoop down at 150 feet 
to douse the first of 10 counties with a pesticide to combat the 
burgeoning mosquito population 
the targeted areas are where high water from the hurricane and 
several inches of rain the following week left standing water that 
creates a perfect breeding haven for mosquitoes 
a total of 807000 acres in the state will be sprayed with the 
chemical dibrom which maj terry biery of the us air force 
reserve called the safest chemical for the project the spray kills 
living mosquitoes but has no effect on mosquito larvae 
the swarms of mosquitoes are presenting problems for residents 
and the mosquitoes were so numerous it was hard for some of the 
cleanup work to be done said pat wright of the state 
department of health and environmental control 
we also had our people out taking what we call landing rate 
counts ms wright said its a warm body who goes out where 
mosquitoes are breeding and stands for a minute counting the number 
of mosquitoes that land on them 
but she said most of the reports came back that the mosquitoes 
were too numerous to count 
the spraying that begins this weekend should be completed in 
eight to nine days depending on weather conditions the 500000 
tab will be picked up by the federal emergency disaster agency with 
hugo disaster funds 
it will be an unusual sight because a c130 airplane with a 
wingspan of 137 feet seldom flies so close to the ground 
the colorless odorless spray poses no danger to humans or pets 
although it can kill bees officials said 
this is one of the safest chemicals we could put out at one 
of the lowest doses we could put out biery said 
after the hurricane struck sept 21 the state health department 
asked the centers for disease control to check for mosquitoborne 
viruses ms wright said 
no viruses were found but local officials reported the mosquito 
population was much greater than normal 
the counties of berkeley dorchester georgetown sumter 
clarendon williamsburg orangeburg horry colleton and charleston 
will be sprayed officials said 
the areas that will be sprayed in charleston county include 
hardhit sullivans island the isle of palms and mcclellanville 
the raid on the mosquitoes will be conducted by crews from the 
907th tactical air group us air force reserve from rickenbacker 
air national guard base in ohio 
