before the first westernmanaged hotel in the east bloc could 
open its doors friday owners had to forage across a grim landscape 
of perpetual shortages import the goods it couldnt find and teach 
communisttaught wholesalers about supply and demand 
they also had to stop the toiletseat thieves 
the opening of 520room warsaw marriott marks completion of the 
first uspolish joint venture signed after the 1987 lifting of 
us trade sanctions imposed in response to the martiallaw 
crackdown of 1981 
it is viewed as a test of the profits and pitfalls awaiting 
major western investors in eastern europe 
rapid political changes provided a timely break for the 
partnership formed by the washingtonbased hotelier the austrian 
ilbau construction company and the polish airlines lot a 
noncommunist government bent on resurrecting the economy has taken 
over and both tourism and business traffic are swiftly growing 
