journalist terry andersons friends and 
colleagues prayed for an end to his special cruelty friday and 
vowed not to forget him at a mass of hope on his 42nd birthday 
his fifth in captivity 
andersons relatives professional colleagues and diplomats 
filled a chapel at georgetown university for an hourlong ceremony 
