manipulated 
he also said some of the people he killed were almost dead 
from being beaten during interrogation 
but some of joyas former comrades told judge flores figueroa 
that joya was the most zealous of torturers who beat drowned or 
suffocated prisoners 
joya has been charged in absentia with premeditated murder in 
the deaths of parada and miranda cpl alcides gomez in the patrol 
that included joya also is charged in the slaying of the two men 
gomez is under arrest 
though joya said he did not know the identities of the men he 
killed his former comrades told the judge that joya was an 
intelligence agent responsible for the capture of specific rebel 
suspects he knew by name 
lt herbert soriano commanded the atlacatl battalion company 
operating north of the capital when parada and miranda were beaten 
or shot to death the two were among eight guerrilla suspects 
captured during an operation around the village of tres ceibas 
according to the testimony of soldiers who took part in the 
operation all eight prisoners were beaten and several were nearly 
drowned by joya over two days of interrogation in the field 
both cpl gomez and another atlacatl soldier eugenio mendez 
testified soriano had given explicit instructions that prisoners 
were not to be tortured gomez said he told joya not to torture the 
prisoners but joya replied if i dont they wont tell us 
anything 
gomez and mendez said soriano was not present when parada and 
miranda were killed they said that after the deaths soriano told 
joya youre in big trouble 
gomez told the judge that after the first man died of the 
beating he expressed concern to joya about problems with the army 
he claimed joya told him dont worry im going to kill them 
all 
in his testimony soriano said two 1st brigade soldiers joya 
and humberto rodriguez were attached to but working 
independently of his atlacatl company 
soriano said a squad from his company accompanied joya and 
rodriguez in making the arrests at tres ceibas he said the squads 
only mission was to give security to the two 1st brigade soldiers 
so they could perform their intelligencegathering duty 
an estimated 70000 people have killed in the 10yearold war 
between leftist rebels and usbacked governments most of the 
