<TEXT>
a european ariane rocket blasted 
off friday night and placed the worlds largest telecommunications 
satellite into orbit 
the 44l rocket lifted off from the european space agency center 
on the northeastern atlantic coast of south america 
less than a halfhour later arianespace a consortium of 11 
european countries said the intelsat vi satellite had been placed 
into orbit 
in the coming days the satellite is to move into position over 
central africa to enter service with the intelsat network of 13 
satellites 
manufactured by nine international companies under the direction 
of the hughes aircraft co of the united states intelsat vi weighs 
9500 pounds and measures 39 feet by 12 feet 
with 24000 simultaneous twoway telephone circuits and three 
color television channels the satellite will relay telephone 
television fax telex and data transmissions 
it is the first of a new generation of five satellites planned 
to be put into service by the washingtonbased international 
telecommunications satellite organization a nonprofit cooperative 
of 117 nations 
the mission marked the 34th launch since 1979 by arianespace 
the fourstage rocket had been scheduled to lift off oct 5 but was 
postponed when technicians found problems in the electrical 
components that operate the vehicles command systems 
arianespace has launched 33 satellites for orders totalling 
214 billion 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

