<TEXT>
stock dealers in new york and chicago were slow 
to warm to the latest innovation in program trading of stocks 
but officials of the new york stock exchange and chicago board 
options exchange said they were satisfied with the lackluster 
firstday trading thursday of socalled stock baskets and 
predicted the new products would become accepted over time 
we had no real expectations of activity that we were aiming 
for said nyse spokeswoman sharon gamsin her exchange traded 
nine of the stock baskets thursday 
but critics said they had doubts about whether the baskets would 
ever catch on they cited bad publicity about program trading a 
strategy involving the simultaneous trading of a range of stocks 
that has been criticized as worsening stock market volatility 
all of the clients are telling us they dont like program 
trading we dont do it said brad weeks a senior vice president 
at donaldson lufkin amp jenrette securities corp 
the baskets essentially are portfolios that allow big investors 
to buy or sell in a single transaction every stock in the 
standard amp poors 500stock index that is aimed at investors who 
want to bet on the direction of the overall stock market without 
picking individual stocks 
investors bet on the overall market now mainly by trading 
stockindex futures and options in the chicago commodities markets 
at the nyse nine baskets were traded thursday at a price of a 
little more than 5 million apiece the chicago options exchange 
handled 14 trades of a cheaper version at about 17 million each 
trading began one day after the securities and exchange 
commission gave provisional sixmonth approval to the baskets 
the nyse sensitive to bad publicity about program trading said 
the baskets were introduced in response to a recommendation of the 
brady commission which investigated the october 1987 stock market 
crash 
its not something we designed to facilitate program 
trading ms gamsin said 
but one brady commission member robert kirby said he was 
unimpressed with the innovation 
the world needs another step toward the commoditization of 
common stocks like it needs an addition to the national debt 
said kirby chairman of capital guardian trust co in los angeles 
trading proceeded smoothly albeit slowly at the new york and 
chicago exchanges except for a miware glitch in nnor softew york 
several market makers and exchange officials said 
the spread between bid and ask prices the difference between 
what market makers will pay for a basket and what they will sell it 
for was narrower than it would be if each of the 500 stocks were 
bought separately making the basket a more efficient way to 
participate in the market according to matthew celebuski vice 
president of futures and options strategy at painewebber inc 
the efficiency of the baskets eventually should attract big 
investors such as pension funds and life insurance companies 
celebuski predicted nyse officials agreed 
we would hope that over time the nine baskets would become 20 
30 50 etc said donald solodar a senior vice president at the 
exchange 
the four firms making a market in the nyses version of the 
market basket which officially is known as the exchange stock 
portfolio were painewebber morgan stanley amp co first boston 
corp and salomon brothers inc 
painewebbers celebuski said he believed basket trading would 
slow the form of program trading known as index arbitrage by 
keeping stocks and futures closer in line 
the software glitch at the new york stock exchange prevented use 
of a mechanism by which investors could sidestep the four 
marketmaking firms and buy or sell a market basket by going 
straight to the specialists who make markets in the 500 stocks 
