<TEXT>
boeing co announced plans friday for a 
reorganization of military and space exploration work to cut losses 
on defense projects and reduce overhead costs on government work 
generally 
boeing spokesman paul binder said the organizational changes 
were largely a matter of redrawing flow charts and executive 
assignments without any change in job assignments or employment 
level at any plant 
many details however have been left to be determined by a 
transition team and there is no target level for savings binder 
said 
he added that a productionhalting strike that began oct 4 by 
the international association of machinists and aerospace workers 
was not a factor in the reorganization 
last year boeing reported 125 million in profits on missiles 
and space systems chiefly the aerospace and electronics division 
and losses of 95 million on military transportation products and 
related systems covering most of the other affected divisions 
effective jan 2 a defense and space group will cover boeing 
military airplanes in wichita kan boeing aerospace and 
electronics and boeing advanced systems both in seattle boeing 
helicopters near philadelphia and argosystems of sunnyvale 
calif near san francisco 
all of boeings commercial airplanes are assembled in seattle 
and the surrounding communities 
boeing work in wichita is being reorganized under a wichita 
branch covering military work and a wichita division of boeing 
commercial airplanes 
work done in wichita now performed under the heading of boeing 
military airplanes is actually 53 percent devoted to production of 
components for the 737 747 757 and 767 commercial plane airframes 
boeing advanced systems will be renamed boeing military 
airplanes with jurisdiction over the wichita branch 
this unified organization structure will increase the 
management focus and facilitate performance improvements in certain 
overhead elements of our current defense and space activities 
boeing chairman frank shrontz said in a prepared statement 
with the moves binder said boeing would be in a better position 
to land what is expected to be a dwindling number of military and 
space exploration contracts 
he denied the changes involved any switch in emphasis between 
boeings commercial side which has recorded record sales and 
profits in recent years and the less successful military side 
we are trying to make ourselves more competitive in the market 
both markets he said 
boeing senior vice president b dan pinick who serves as 
president of aerospace and electronics was named president of the 
group by shrontz 
john dempster chief design engineer for boeing military 
airplanes was named vice president of that division and general 
manager of the new wichita branch 
cg king currently president of boeing advanced systems 
becomes president of boeing military airplanes 
robert dryden now president of boeing military airplanes was 
named head of the wichita division and executive vice president of 
boeing commercial airplanes 
