scandinavian airlines system swissair 
and finnair announced friday they had reached a farreaching 
cooperation agreement to strengthen their positions in the 1990s 
and open the way for increased travel to eastern europe 
sas jointly owned by sweden norway and denmark the swiss 
carrier swissair and finlands finnair said in a joint statement 
their aim was to create a competitive service system 
they said they expected flights between the nordic capitals to 
increase by around 30 percent and give passengers direct access to 
finnairs daily flights to moscow and leningrad in the soviet union 
under the agreement which will take effect next march sas and 
finnair will buy shares in each other but continue to operate as 
separate companies finnair also will buy a part of hotel chain 
international continental hotels which is owned 40 percent by sas 
intercontinental hotels 
last month sas and swissair announced an agreement aimed at 
establishing a combined route system by next summer 
sas based in stockholm has actively been seeking links with 
other airlines managing director jan carlzon has predicted that no 
more than five major european carriers will remain by the mid1990s 
in the past year sas has bought 10 percent of texas air corp 
as a way to link up with continental airlines a texas air 
subsidiary it also has purchased 25 percent of airlines of britain 
holdings plc owner of four british carriers and formed a joint 
venture with all nippon airways of japan 
