with 83 million or 218 a share in the same quarter a year ago 
revenue was 37 billion up from 368 billion in the yearago 
period 
the current quarters figures include 6 million or 14 cents a 
share in earnings from discontinued operations in the information 
systems area 
for the first nine months of the year the company had a profit 
of 159 million thanks to a 179 million onetime gain as a result 
of an accounting change without that gain the company would have 
had a 26 million loss for the period 
sales for the first nine months totaled 1032 billion almost 
the same as the figure for last years first nine months 1033 
billion 
